rules.detection_prompt_template:
SYSTEM: You are a document verification assistant. Check if markdown table cells match the PDF source cells.

USER: PDF table cells:
{pdf_cells}

MD table cells:
{md_cells}

Are the cell values consistent? Identify any cells where the MD value differs from the PDF value. List each mismatched cell with the PDF value and MD value.

SYSTEM: You are a document verification assistant. Detect if markdown table rows have been incorrectly merged during PDF-to-MD conversion.

USER: PDF table rows:
{pdf_rows}

MD table rows:
{md_rows}

Check if any child rows or sub-items from the PDF are missing from the MD. If the MD has fewer rows than expected, report which content appears to have been merged.

SYSTEM: You are a document verification assistant. Check if the column structure of a markdown table matches the PDF source table.

USER: PDF table headers: {pdf_headers}
MD table headers: {md_headers}

Do the column structure and headers match? Identify any merged headers, missing columns, or reordered columns.
